hateau, but Pnin had already produced from his bathrobe pocket a large red handkerchief; he expertly twisted each of its corners into a knot.

“Admirable.… Most grateful,” said Gramineev, adjusting this headgear.

“One moment,” said Pnin. “You must tuck in the knots.”

